      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Determines if the DFA is valid. A valid DFA has ONE legitimate transition leaving every state for '0' and '1'
        Returns:
        True if the DFA is valid (as defined), false otherwise.

      • MatchesRegex

        public boolean MatchesRegex(java.lang.String regex)
        Determine whether the DFA accepts the strings it should.
        Parameters:
        regex - The regex to check strings against.
        Returns:
        True if the DFA only accepts the strings it should and rejects the strings it should. False otherwise.

      • testOnAll

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Boolean> testOnAll()
        Test all strings as long as the DFAs pumping length and tests them for acceptance by the DFA.
        Returns:
        A map of strings of the pumping length mapped to a boolean representing whether or not they are accepted by the DFA.
